cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CGT. 

The paper deals with complexity measures of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of unambiguous certificates and their connection to sensitivity suggests information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) as possible sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational geometry and topology (cs.CGT) in the context of the Clique vs. Independent Set problem.
